Coaxial Cable (Coax)
Coaxial cable carries signals of higher frequency ranges than those in twisted pair cable.

41

Coaxial cable has a central core conductor of copper wire enclosed in an insulating sheath.

Insulating sheath encased in an outer conductor of metal foil.

The outer metallic wrapping serves both as a shield against noise and as the second
conductor, which completes the circuit.

This outer conductor is also enclosed in an insulating sheath, and the whole cable is
protected by a plastic cover.
Coaxial cables are categorized by their Radio Government (RG) ratings. Each RG number
